s:\n*   **Title I (Management & Operations):** Enacted funding of $1.88 billion, a 37.7% increase over FY2018, driven largely by financial systems modernization.\n*   **Title II (Security, Enforcement, & Investigations):** The largest component, receiving $40.00 billion. This title covers Customs and Border Protection (CBP), ICE, TSA, the Coast Guard, and the Secret Service. Funding increased by 4.1% over the request and 1.2% over FY2018.\n*   **Title III (Protection, Preparedness, Response, & Recovery):** Enacted at $18.27 billion, a 42.3% increase over the request, primarily due to the elevated DRF allocation for FEMA.\n*   **Title IV (R&D, Training, & Services):** Received $1.62 billion, a modest 3.3% increase over the request.\n*   **Title V (General Provisions):** Included $303 million in rescissions and provisions directing $300 million of unobligated DRF balances to offset new appropriations.\n\nThe report also highlights the Department's transition to a Common Appropriations Structure (CAS) to improve transparency and standardize budgeting across components. Finally, the document provides an educational appendix defining key budgetary concepts such as budget authority, obligations, outlays, discretionary versus mandatory spending, and the mechanics of the Budget Control Act caps and adjustments, which were critical in authorizing the increased disaster relief funding for FY2019.", refusal=None, role='assistant', annotations=None, audio=None, function_call=None, tool_calls=[], reasoning=None), stop_reason=None, token_ids=None)], created=1783664909, model='Qwen3.5-27B', object='chat.completion', service_tier=None, system_fingerprint=None, usage=CompletionUsage(completion_tokens=758, prompt_tokens=8426, total_tokens=9184, completion_tokens_details=None, prompt_tokens_details=None), prompt_logprobs=None, prompt_token_ids=None, kv_transfer_params=None)

